this past month i was fortunate enough to go to chile and complete among the best of the best. unfortunately i fell a little bit short in my second round but i’m super grateful to have gotten the opportunity to compete at this event and take home memories i’ll cherish for the rest of my life.

feeling extra thankful today!! thankful for the opportunities i’m given, thankful for the people around me, and thankful for all the support i get. i’m very blessed to have the best coach’s @vitalyokinawa @alexokinawa blessed to have the best team @okinawadojobykaratebros the best sponsor @afsgear.usa and the support from my family and friends! can’t wait for more❤️‍🔥
